<br>
Narve Vitalievitch sat relaxingly behind his huge desk and pondered the recent events in the colonial capital.  New Hague was a new venue for the Dark Enterprises and acquiring its market was crucial for the supraplanetary corporation.  Earth3 was a gateway to Old Earth from the resource-rich Outer Regions and Dark Enterprises was determined to become the dominant transporter of cargo in the region. <br>
<br>
The particular event Narve was thinking about was the new governor that has been appointed from Old Earth. Dark Enterprises' political influence had to be extended once more, and the documents that Aria was delivering were supposed to ensure that the new deputy governor was compliant to corporation's requests.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mr. Vitalievitch, Aria is here to see you.&quot;  The secretary informed him.<br>
<br>
The dark-haired businessman didn't reply to his assistant - Aria always had access to his office. Narve turned to face the door and waited for it to open.<br>
<br>
Aria gently pushed open the door.  &quot;I delivered those documents like you asked.&quot;  She smiled warmly.  &quot;The man just nodded his head to me before he left.&quot;  She approached his desk.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Good. Michael Hauser will soon be in our pocket,&quot; Narve acknowledged emotionlessly. &quot;I see you haven't fed yet, your appearance is very dangerous,&quot; he continued looking into Aria's sunken eyes.<br>
<br>
Aria dropped her eyes with a frown.  &quot;I didn't have time.&quot;  She whispered.<br>
<br>
He chuckled &quot;I see,&quot; and continued to examine her pale face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Once I left our contact I ran into two women.  They were both Vampires but of a different sort.  One of blood the other of mind.  I am supposed to meet them tomorrow.  Perhaps they would be a good asset to our company?&quot;  She raised her eyes to meet his steel blues.<br>
<br>
&quot;Childe, childe,&quot; the fleshstealer shook his head &quot;just because they are vampires doesn't mean they are useful.&quot; &quot;However, presence of more of our kind could compromise *us*,&quot; Narve stood up and approached Aria &quot;have a meeting with them, find out why they are here and assess their threat or usefulness.&quot; &quot;And please,&quot; he took her small hand into his &quot;feed my dear, you are compromising the Masquerade&quot;<br>
<br>
She sighed deeply.  &quot;I know.  Its still difficult to kill.  I will look for one perhaps that is already dying.&quot;<br>
<br>
Narve shrugged his shoulders, as if saying &quot;I don't care how, just feed&quot;<br>
